column5: I unpacked and put all the gear away from the trip up to Temagami and flipped a coin later this morning whether to sit and watch Coronation Street with my sweetie or go out and try hunting down a Muskie.....the coin toss won the Muskie outing so out I went.....  Not sure but this gal may have been hooked before as her upper lip line pretty scarred....
One of thoes trick coins eh?...
hope my wife doesn't read this or I'll get an   whoopin'
That's a real beautiful Ottawa R. musky.... Congrats Steve Jacques
Real nice musky! Looks over 45 inches, did you measure it?
Nice fish, I really got to go muskie fishing at some point. Never been.
yup me too! i gotta get out there fer some musky, i mean i have had some nice pike but a big ol' 50 inch musky would be quite the experiance.
Beyond the mangled lip that's a nice clean lookin' fish. (You made the right choice,  )
Sometimes I find you just have to keep flippin' until the coin finally lands the right way.    Certainly landed the right way for you, nice fish!
